setup:
For a given process, make sure the CloudWatch Agent is installed on the instance (follow
  https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonCloudWatch/latest/monitoring/Install-CloudWatch-Agent.html)
  then use the following Cloudwatch Agent config, replacing PID_PATH with the relevant .pid file
  and providing the same path to the PidPath parameter in the template:

  ```json
  {
    "agent":
      {
         "run_as_user": "cwagent"
      },
    "metrics":
    {
      "metrics_collected": {
         "procstat": [
           {
             "pid_file": "PID_PATH",
             "measurement": [
                 "pid_count"
             ]
           }
         ]
       },
      "append_dimensions": {
        "InstanceId": "${aws:InstanceId}"
      }
    }
  }
  ```

